h3. Problem Definition
Our [Configuring JIRA application options - Administering JIRA Server Applications|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/AdminJIRAServer070/Configuring+JIRA+application+options] docs we state that there is the following option:
{quote}
|| Setting || Description ||
| Accept remote API calls | Controls whether to allow remote client access (via XML-RPC or SOAP) to this JIRA installation, for authenticated users.
{color:green}_Default:_ *OFF*{color} |
{quote}

However, this option is not available in JIRA 7 as JIRA's SOAP and XML-RPC remote APIs were removed in JIRA 7.0 for Server as per [SOAP and XML-RPC API Deprecation Notice - Atlassian Developers|https://developer.atlassian.com/jiradev/latest-updates/soap-and-xml-rpc-api-deprecation-notice].

h3. Suggested Solution
Remove this option from the documentation, and if possible leave a note regarding why it was removed.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-45766].
  {panel}

For Cloud instances, it comes bundled with add-ons and applications.

Some of the add-ons come with some default add-on custom fields (such as JIRA Capture, Tempo) and JIRA Software application comes with some issue types and custom fields as well, the fields are there even the instance is not licensed for the said add-ons and software. Some of the field is not editable (locked) and some of them will return after a restart.

Administrator would like to have the ability to remove the custom field in the case where they do not subscribe for the application OR even better, not to have any field or configuration deployed if the add-on is not licensed.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-45759].
  {panel}

With the new changes coming for JIRA 7 I think it's a very bad idea to exclude Agile boards from Business project types. I've done JIRA work for two very large, public companies and I know for a fact that they have business projects that aren't remotely related to software but still use Agile methods. I even have a personal instance of JIRA which I use to track my work and I want to use Agile boards for non-software projects. I do think it is a good idea to make Source Management project specific.

Allow us to pick and choose which projects get Agile and Source Management but don't bundle it into "Project Types".

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-45757].
  {panel}

h3. Problem Definition
The tutorials on developer.atlassian.com such as [Adding content to the JIRA View Issue page|https://developer.atlassian.com/jiradev/jira-platform/guides/issues/tutorial-adding-content-to-the-jira-view-issue-page] do not work on JIRA 7 due to the changes in the API.

h3. Suggested Solution
Update the tutorials or create new tutorials in order to create add-ons compatible with JIRA 7.
 
h3. Workaround 
Follow the tutorials but modify any necessary code as per [Preparing for JIRA 7.0 - Atlassian Developers|https://developer.atlassian.com/jiradev/latest-updates/preparing-for-jira-7-0]. For example, replace {{com.atlassian.crowd.embedded.api.User}} with {{com.atlassian.jira.user.ApplicationUser}}

